{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-05-07T16:50:19Z","content":"BECAUSE THERE IS NO REASONS FOR TREATING A POLYTECHNIC GRADUATE AS A SECOND CLASS NIGERIA STUDENT.","like_count":0,"author_name":"OGBONNA OFODILE","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91906852"},{"created_at":"2014-05-10T15:43:47Z","content":"Good","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hassan Abdullahi Haruna","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/93133760"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T10:19:06Z","content":"Having been at home for close to a year doing nothing,as well as the lives of many students been cut short and send to an early grave.......................the Govt of Nigeria is doing and as well saying nothing as regards to the demand of ASUP...........something need to be urgently done before many things will go wrong.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chukwuani Uzoamaka P.","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91656299"},{"created_at":"2014-05-03T15:34:48Z","content":"Uduh Ugochukwu a final year Polytechnic student having seen the lives of two of his vibrant classmates cut short in a space of 7 days due to the lingering ASUP & COESU strike Joins the campaign #EndASUPstrikeNow with all other Nigerian Polytechnic & Colleges of Education Students\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nPolytechnic students across Nigeria has been at have been at home for almost a year starting from April 29th when the 7days warning strike came to an end and the  Academic Staff Union Of Polytechnics (ASUP) proceeded to an indefinite strike producing a 13 point demand that they wanted the FG to Look into. Ranging from the re negotiation of the 2001 agreement between her ad FG that was due in 2009 and movement to CONTISS 15 salary scale for their workers on the lower care lasted among others.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nDuring Negotiation the FG asked ASUP to pick out 4 most pressing issues that needed attention most so that they can tackle as a sign to show that they are committed to negotiating with ASUP. Of the Four items Chosen only the establishment of Governing Councils for the Polytechnic which is more or less a political exercise which is used to settle the different political interest that arise from the party of different alliance was completed 100%.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIn the last 220 days that the polytechnics has been on strike, over 100 Polytechnic Students across the nation has lost their lives in one way or the other Most especially final year students, due to the fact that they were at the wrong places at the wrong times. We are not saying that death is evitable but if students were in session most of these lost Graduates (RIP) will either be serving their father land or be in a different places or circumstance that might have speared their lives and delay death till another day.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAs  a Nigerian, and a  Polytechnic Student I demand these from my President.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThat ASUP Strike should be called off with immediate effect!\r\n\r\nThat the President as a matter of urgency, He has a round table with ASUP Like their Counter Part ASUU in order to move Polytechnic education to the next level.\r\n\r\nThat the Dichotomy between HND & BSc be treated as a matter of National urgency.\r\n\r\nThat Polytechnic student should be treated like Nigerian student and not second class citizens.\r\n\r\n That plans are put in Motion that all quallifed finalists be considered for youth service in the next available Batch after their exams.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ugo Uduh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57123816"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T11:13:14Z","content":"It is our fight.......we have to stand and own our responsibility cause if we(polytechnic students) don't stand up for our selves.............nobody will","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chukwuani Uzoamaka P.","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91656299"},{"created_at":"2014-05-03T14:38:56Z","content":"Polytechnic Students are been Treated as second Class Citizens the Fed Govt Should pay more attention to them","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ugo Uduh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57123816"}]}